column5: Got up to Kenlea for the annual end of summer fishing/swill (hic) the water temps are still a little warm for the walters (around 60 f) but there was a few around the first day all we found were some smallies,  and of course Uncle Bucks wee gobie.   That was Friday, the wet weather and clouds on Saturday seem to bring out the walleye    ....and the fry pan shots....   one largemouth  and these guys dropped in to see if the fish were in the river  alot of this  and not enough this  a very good time looking forward to next year!
Only a real man cooks with pink tongs!   Nice fish!  Thanks for the report
love the OV shot!  Few of us around!  Cheers!
Nice! ...tackle used this time of year?-skdds
Looks like a great time, beautiful country up there.
Brings back memories, stayed there many times.

Nothing wrong with pink tongs, its his pink thongs we are concerned about. Yes It is beautiful up there, going back at the end of October. The fish were caught mostly on a simple jig and minnow, or just a minnow on a hook with a split shot. Good times......
Great report and pics Grog Love the shot of the hot pan.... ummmm fresh fish Thanks for sharing your trip with us!!! Leechman
Great report. Looks and sounds like some great fishing and good eating. Thanks for sharing.
